net.varkhan.base.containers
Interface Index

All Known Implementing Classes:
Index.Empty, Index.Enumerate, Index.Range, Index.Sequence, Index.Singleton
public interface Index

A bidirectional iterator over an Indexed content container.

IndexIterators enumerate valid long indexes for the contents of an Indexed container, allowing both forward and backward traversal.

Nested Class Summary
static class Index.Empty
          An empty index iterator (whose hasNext() and hasPrevious() methods always return false, and current(), next() and previous() methods throw an Index.InvalidIndexException).
static class Index.Enumerate
          An enumeration iterator, that returns all indexes in an array, in order.
static class Index.InvalidIndexException
          An exception thrown upon lookup of a non-existing index.

An Index or an Indexed content container may throw this exception when asked to retrieve an object at an invalid index, or an index that does not have associated content.
static class Index.Range
          A range iterator, that returns all indexes in a range.
static class Index.Sequence
          A sequence iterator, that returns all the indexes of a series of Indexes, in order.
static class Index.Singleton
          A singleton iterator, that returns a single element.
